title: Frode Gjerstad -- Paal Nilssen-Love Project - Hasselt (2014)
description: Frode Gjerstad / Paal Nilssen-Love Project Hasselt 2014 - Not Two Records: MW909-2 http://www.nottwo.com/mw909 * Frode Gjerstad : alto saxophone, Bb clarinet, bass clarinet * Sabir Mateen : tenor saxophone, flute, clarinet * Peter Friis-Nielsen: electric bass * Paal Nilssen-Love : drums http://www.efi.group.shef.ac.uk/mgjersta.html http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frode_Gjerstad http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sabir_Mateen http://www.allmusic.com/artist/peter-friis-nielsen-mn0001231539 http://www.paalnilssen-love.com/ Recorded live by Frode Gjerstad at Kunstcentrum Belgie, Hasselt, Belgium, September 23, 2006. http://www.kunstencentrumbelgie.com/ http://www.hasselt.be/ http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hasselt http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hasselt Reviews ~~~~~~~ By Ed Pettersen http://www.freejazzblog.org/2014/04/frode-gjerstad-hasselt-nottwo-2014.html [...] Highly, highly recommended stuff. If this is your first introduction to Frode Gjerstad’s work there could almost be no better place to start but don’t stop here. He rarely repeats himself and has a vast catalog well worth researching. His work on this recording includes sax, flute and occasional clarinet and he’s highly proficient on each. Kudos to the entire unit on this record. They could well be considered a classic line up in years to come whether they record again or not. That’s how good they sound together here. I could prattle on and on and wax more poetically but it wouldn’t add anything more to this gem without ruining your own discovery of this set and possibly overstating it. Simply, check it out. I think you’ll dig it. As we Scandinavians say, “Skol!” -- Par Guillaume Belhomme (fr)
